data.title: Arrondissement of Montargis
data.text:
Arrondissement in Centre-Val de Loire, France

The arrondissement of Montargis is an arrondissement of France in the Loiret department in the Centre-Val de Loire region. It has 125 communes.[2] Its population is 170,285 (2016), and its area is 2,657.2 km2 (1,026.0 sq mi).[3]

History

[edit]

The arrondissement of Montargis was created in 1800.[4]

As a result of the reorganisation of the cantons of France which came into effect in 2015, the borders of the cantons are no longer related to the borders of the arrondissements. The cantons of the arrondissement of Montargis were, as of January 2015:[5]

Amilly

Bellegarde

Briare

Châlette-sur-Loing

Château-Renard

Châtillon-Coligny

Châtillon-sur-Loire

Courtenay

Ferrières-en-Gâtinais

Gien

Lorris

Montargis
